<br>
Sigh<br>
<br>
I don't think I've ever died in a post-hell level before, I'd always heard people complain about how much xp they lost, but I just about crapped my pants when I saw how far back into 40 I was. I shelled out 500pp for a 56 res and as far as I'm concerned it was the best money ever spent. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, after this I was ALOT more caucious, I got a lvl 57 SK friend of mine to come help me hunt them, and even with him along we got beaten to within an inch of our lives by griffins that evening.. those things are just MEAN, and it can be really hard to avoid adds.. but after I got those two eggs right off the bat, I only found one more in about 10 griffin kills.. &lt;sigh&gt;<br>
<br>
Is there anyway to outrun these guys if your inital snare fails? I would really like to not have to risk a friends life just to get this last egg, but man are they fast... is wolf form quick enough to get far enough ahead that you can snare them?<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 41 wizard, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwizxeg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WizXeg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/01 6:30:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Griffins</span><hr size=1> They are extremely fast, SoW speed, since they do SoW themselves.<br>
