<br>
Make sure you have Sow on before you try to fight these things.  They run at sow speeds themselves, and BoF sometimes just isn't enough to keep these things off of your tail.  Also, have a shadowstep/fade/gate memmed, these guys can and will root you, if that happens you're screwed.  Your only chance is to Shadowstep out of the area and gate away.  Don't bother to try to finish the fight at that point. <p><A HREF="http://doomwisper.hypermart.net/dae/rhal.html"><IMG  SRC="http://doomwisper.hypermart.net/Rhal/sig1.jpg" border=0></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/01 8:16:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Griffins</span><hr size=1> One of the fun things about fighting the Snow Griffins is the cute little druid spells they cast.  Its so precious seeing that tiny blast go off on you while they make themselves easier to kite by stopping to cast.  Ooh, you did 70 to me.... 625... oh, you did 15 to me.... 625.  Heh Heh <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uevaldamriveneficus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evaldamri Veneficus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 6:04:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Griffins - Post 50 advice</span><hr size=1> Depending on your level I would just do what I do with <br>
all ranger/ drOOd mobs...<br>
<br>
Atols till it sticks.... This kills SOW or makes it at least out runnable.   Use Draught of Jiva-this is your main weapon.<br>
If it gets on you use a stun to give you a moment to get atols locked down on it.<br>
<br>
Maybe even open up with the markars followed by the atols.<br>
I'm not sure how MR these guys are but I'm guessing not overly so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugibwigglestump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gib Wigglestump</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.foobarbaz.com/reviction/rv.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 1:19:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/entropy34/runecog.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Griffins - Post 50 advice</span><hr size=1> <br>
